# Codex Writer Findings — StaffOrdersMobile
Chain: staffordersmobile-260412-123531-7231

## Findings
1. [P1] Missing SCS urgency and chip derivation for Fix 1 — In `pages/StaffOrdersMobile/staffordersmobile.jsx` the helper area at lines 376-378 still jumps directly from `formatClockTime` to `getAgeMinutes`, and the `OrderGroupCard` data section at lines 2018-2025 still defines only `jumpChips` before continuing into `legacySummaryLines`. The required Fix 1 values `getUrgencyLevel`, `URGENCY_IDENTITY_STYLE`, `SCS_SOLID_CHIP`, `scsChips`, `scsOldestActionable`, `scsUrgency`, and `scsHighlightKey` are absent, so the collapsed table card cannot compute the required pastel identity background, longest-chip highlight, or the new actionable/non-actionable chip set. FIX: add the Fix 1 helper/constants near `formatClockTime`, then compute `scsChips` and the derived urgency/highlight values immediately after `jumpChips`.
2. [P1] Collapsed table header still renders the legacy compact layout — The active `group.type === "table"` branch at lines 2181-2205 still uses the old `space-y-2` header with an inline ownership icon/button (2185-2193), a dark table pill with white text (2194), an optional zone chip (2195), and no 84px identity wrapper or 78x54 pastel identity block. This misses the required outside overlap ownership badge, always-dark 26px table number, free-table green outline, and wrapped right-side `scsChips` layout from Fix 1. FIX: replace the entire collapsed table header block with the specified identity-wrapper + identity block + right-zone `scsChips` layout, remove the zone chip from the collapsed header, and show `HALL_UI_TEXT.noActions` only when `scsChips` is empty.
3. [P1] Jump chips were not moved to expanded view — The always-visible header still renders `jumpChips` at line 2205 and still uses the old `setIsExpanded(true); scrollToSection(...)` handler, while the expanded table content starts at lines 2230-2247 with no jump-chip row at its top. That leaves jump chips visible in collapsed state and missing from expanded state, which is the opposite of Fix 1. FIX: remove the header-level `jumpChips` render, then add the specified `jumpChips.length > 0` button row as the first element inside the expanded table fragment, keeping `HALL_CHIP_STYLES` unchanged and dropping `setIsExpanded(true)` from the chip click handler.

