+2. [P1] Collapsed table header still renders the legacy compact layout — The active `group.type === "table"` branch at lines 2181-2205 still uses the old `space-y-2` header with an inline ownership icon/button (2185-2193), a dark table pill with white text (2194), an optional zone chip (2195), and no 84px identity wrapper or 78x54 pastel identity block. This misses the required outside overlap ownership badge, always-dark 26px table number, free-table green outline, and wrapped right-side `scsChips` layout from Fix 1. FIX: replace the entire collapsed table header block with the specified identity-wrapper + identity block + right-zone `scsChips` layout, remove the zone chip from the collapsed header, and show `HALL_UI_TEXT.noActions` only when `scsChips` is empty.
